      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MOUNT BARKER BOY (6) is a lightly raced but progressive colt who has won both starts off year-long spell. Overcame a second row draw to strike first up before leading to score well last time at Melton. Draws wider but can continue to work through his grades. FICTION FILE (2) hasn't been seen since the Vicbred Super Series Final in November but was readied with two trials, winning the latest. Her lone win came the only time she attempted this distance. Can be competitive from an ideal draw. BAKERS BANDIT (4) has had four weeks off must be considered after placing in his last three outings. GIDGETT KAY (3) won on debut before a midfield finish behind MOUNT BARKER BOY last start. Draws lower so is a first four hope.",
